[2] Pakistan, 2nd case confirmed -- media report
Date: Fri 8 Feb 2019
Source: Pakistan Today [edited]
https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2019/02/08/health-dg-confirms-presence-of-poliovirus-in-faisalabad/


Health Director General (DG) Dr. Munir Ahmed on Friday [8 Feb 2019] confirmed the presence of poliovirus in Faisalabad. As per details, the samples collected from Achkera Pumping Station turned out to be positive for poliovirus.

The crippling virus has been reported in Lahore and Rawalpindi, and it was earlier detected in Faisalabad back in 2016. "An anti-polio drive will kick-off from [18 Feb 2019] in Faisalabad, Lahore and Rawalpindi to eradicate the crippling virus from the areas," Dr. Munir said. He appealed to parents to ensure the vaccination of their children against polio and save their future while also helping Pakistan to become a polio-free country.

On Thursday [7 Feb 2019], the Prime Minister's Focal Person for Polio Eradication Babar Bin Atta had confirmed that the 2nd polio case of the year [2019] had surfaced in Bannu, where a 2-year-old boy had been diagnosed with the crippling virus. He had said that Bannu was one of the areas where parents usually refused to have polio drops administered to their children.

